theorem P2_implies_closure_eq_closure_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A → closure (A : Set X) = closure (interior A) := by
  intro hP2
  -- First inclusion: `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h₁ : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
    have hsubset : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
      -- From `P2`, we have `A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A))`,
      -- and the latter is contained in `closure (interior A)`.
      exact (hP2.trans interior_subset)
    exact closure_mono hsubset
  -- Second inclusion: `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A`.
  have h₂ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
    closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A)
  exact subset_antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P2 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A → closure (A : Set X) = closure (interior A) := by
  intro hP2
  have hP1 : Topology.P1 A := (Topology.P2_implies_P1 (X := X) (A := A)) hP2
  exact (Topology.P1_iff_closure_eq_closure_interior (X := X) (A := A)).1 hP1
